TY  - JOUR
AU  - Price, Joseph
AU  - Wolfers, Justin
T1  - Racial Discrimination Among NBA Referees
PY  - 2010
Y1  - 2010/11/01
DO  - 10.1162/qjec.2010.125.4.1859
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 125
IS  - 4
SP  - 1859
EP  - 1887
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - The NBA provides an intriguing place to assess discrimination: referees and players are involved in repeated interactions in a high-pressure setting, with referees making split-second decisions that might allow implicit racial biases to become evident. We find that more personal fouls are awarded against players when they are officiated by an opposite-race officiating crew than when they are officiated by an own-race refereeing crew. These biases are sufficiently large so that they affect the outcome of an appreciable number of games. Our results do not distinguish whether the bias stems from the actions of white or black referees.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1162/qjec.2010.125.4.1859
ER  - 



