TY  - JOUR
AU  - Chassang, Sylvain
AU  - Miquel, Gerard Padró I
T1  - Conflict and Deterrence Under Strategic Risk*
PY  - 2010
Y1  - 2010/11/01
DO  - 10.1162/qjec.2010.125.4.1821
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 125
IS  - 4
SP  - 1821
EP  - 1858
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - We examine the determinants of cooperation and the effectiveness of deterrence when fear is a motive for conflict.We contrast results obtained in a complete information setting with those obtained in a setting with strategic risk, where players have different information about their environment. These two strategic settings allow us to identify and distinguish the role of predatory and preemptive incentives as determinants of cooperation and conflict. In our model, weapons unambiguously facilitate peace under complete information. In contrast, under strategic risk, we show that increases in weapon stocks can have a nonmonotonic effect on the sustainability of cooperation. We also show that under strategic risk, asymmetry in military strength can facilitate peace, and that anticipated peacekeeping interventions may improve incentives for peaceful behavior.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1162/qjec.2010.125.4.1821
ER  - 



